sub_title: Health innovator through effective education and communication
summary: Yolanda M. Sanchez Castro is a professional in communication and media studies, that outstands for her commitment to Health Quality Managing programs. In her early career, she developed marketing campaigns about health care and healthy lifestyle, an experience that gained her a deeper understanding of Mexicans health consumption. She is a lead auditor in different ISO norms and has led the accreditation process for clinical laboratories. Yolanda was chair of the Swedish Network for International Health, from 2018 to 2019, a position that has allowed her to have a closer perspective of the Swedish Global Health approach. She was nominated for the Women in Global Health chapter Sweden, and she is now part of the Young Innovators Coalition for Global Health. Yolanda recently graduated from the MSc in Global Health at Gothenburg University. During her graduation project, she investigated the association between parental psychosocial status and child BMI with data from the Amsterdam Born Children and their Development Study at the Vrije Universiteit. She currently lives in the Netherlands and is looking for opportunities to continue contributing to decreasing the gap between health research and common knowledge.
